casebody.data:
Rolf ROSENDAHL, Appellant,
v.
MISSOURI DEPARTMENT OF REVENUE, Respondent. WD 80452 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: November 7, 2017
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied December 14, 2017 Rolf Rosendahl, Kansas City, MO, Appellant Acting Pro Se. Garrick Aplin, Jefferson City, MO, Counsel for Respondent. Before Division One: Cynthia L. Martin, P.J., James Edward Welsh, and Karen King Mitchell, JJ.

ORDER

Per Curiam:

Appellant Rolf Rosendahl ("Rosendahl") appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Jackson County denying his Petition for Expungement ("Petition"), which sought to expunge all of Rosendahl's driving records held by the Missouri Department of Revenue. Rosendahl now asserts two points on appeal. We affirm. A memorandum setting forth the reasons for this order has been provided to the parties. Rule 84.16(b).
